# Frontend Must Map To Dashboard Control

When implementing or changing any frontend feature in this project, enforce these checks first:

1. Confirm the feature has a matching control in dashboard/admin panel.
2. If dashboard control does not exist, do not finish feature silently.
3. Add the required dashboard control as part of the same task, or mark task blocked until dashboard support is added.
4. Document control key/name and expected effect on UI behavior.

## Required Workflow

- Identify feature toggle/config source before coding frontend behavior.
- Verify dashboard can enable/disable or configure the feature.
- Wire frontend to the control state (API/config/store), not hardcoded flags.
- Keep behavior backward compatible if control value is missing.

## Example

```ts
// Bad: hardcoded behavior with no dashboard control
const showNewBidFlow = true;

// Good: behavior follows dashboard-provided control
const showNewBidFlow = dashboardConfig?.features?.newBidFlow === true;
```
